Product Vision: AlphaMomentum RecommenderGoal: To provide entry-level traders with a curated list of 4–5 stocks that balance aggressive price velocity with systematic risk suppression.1. Product Core CapabilitiesAutomated Scanning: Scans the broader market for high-velocity price action backed by institutional volume.Risk-Adjusted Ranking: Filters out "overextended" stocks to identify low-risk entry points (the pullback).Sentiment Overlay: Integrates derivative market data (Put/Call ratios) to detect potential momentum traps before they happen.Dynamic Exit Guardrails: Generates real-time stop-loss and take-profit levels based on historical volatility.2. The Logic Funnel (Pipeline Architecture)The system processes market data through three distinct layers to move from ~8,000 tickers to the "Final 5."Layer 1: The Liquidity & Quality GateMarket Cap: $> \$2$ Billion (Mid to Large Cap).Volume Profile: Average Daily Volume (90-day) $> 1,000,000$ shares.Price Floor: Stock Price $> \$10.00$ to avoid penny stock manipulation.Layer 2: The Momentum EngineTrend Confirmation: $Price > EMA_{50}$ and $EMA_{50} > EMA_{200}$.Relative Strength Index (RSI): Between $60$ and $75$.ADX (Trend Strength): $> 25$.Layer 3: Risk & Sentiment Filtering (The De-Risker)This layer utilizes the Put/Call (P/C) Ratio to measure market positioning.IndicatorThresholdLogicPut/Call Ratio$< 0.80$Bullish: Confirms the momentum is supported by options traders.Put/Call Ratio$> 1.20$Warning: High hedging or bearish sentiment; likely a "momentum trap."Relative Volume$> 2.0$High Conviction: Confirms institutional participation in the move.3. The Scoring AlgorithmStocks that pass the filters are ranked using a proprietary Momentum-Quality Score (MQS):$$MQS = \left( \frac{\Delta Price_{6M}}{\sigma_{Volatility}} \right) \times \left( \frac{1}{PC_{Ratio}} \right)$$Numerator: Rewards high returns with low standard deviation (smooth trends).Denominator: Penalizes high Put/Call ratios (bearish sentiment).4. Feature Set: "The Daily 5" RecommendationsThe end product should output a clean dashboard with 4–5 cards. Each card includes:Ticker Analysis ViewThe Catalyst: Brief AI-generated summary of why the stock is moving (e.g., Earnings Beat, FDA Approval).Entry Zone: The "Buy" range, defined as the area between the $EMA_{9}$ and $EMA_{21}$ on a daily chart.The Exit Plan:Hard Stop: $Entry - (2 \times ATR_{14})$.Profit Target 1: $Entry + (3 \times ATR_{14})$.Sentiment Gauge: Visual representation of the Put/Call Ratio relative to its 30-day average.5. Technical Requirements & Data InputsTo build this, the system requires the following data streams:L1 Market Data: Real-time price, volume, and OHLC.Options Flow Data: To calculate the Equity Put/Call Ratio per ticker.Technical Library: Integration with libraries like Pandas-TA or TA-Lib for indicator calculations ($RSI, ADX, ATR$).